- You may modify the software for your own personal, non-commercial use.
- You may study the source code and learn from it.
- You may develop and distribute your own projects, mods, or applications
  that depend on or interface with this software, provided they do not
  include or bundle the software itself.
- You may require end-users to download this software separately from the
  official distribution channel as a prerequisite for your projects.

